</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="640">2.1.2. Import</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets has an <a href="/en/data/importing-data/ElasticSync">import tool</a>, which you can use to import properties.
The idea is simple.
Rather than manually saving property data in plentymarkets, you’ll enter the same information into a CSV file and then import this file into your system.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the <strong>Properties</strong> import type. The fields that you can use for mapping and matching are described on the page of the manual of the import type <a href="/en/data/importing-data/sync-types/elasticSync-properties">Properties</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="660">2.1.3. Catalogue</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Have you already started using the new catalogue tool to transmit your product data to a market like Amazon or OTTO? If so, then you can create properties directly within the catalogue assistant and link them to the marketplace.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Learn more using the <a href="/en/markets/amazon/variation-data-export">Amazon catalogue assistant</a> as an example.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="800">2.2. Searching for existing properties</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Previously created properties are displayed in an overview.
You can use filters to narrow down the search results and only see the properties that meet specific criteria.
You can combine as many search filters as you like.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for properties:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
